Sex in the Stone Age

History Documentary hosted by Adrian Finighan, published by National Geographic in 2012 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

Sex in the Stone Age
A fragment of a pinky bone and a tooth twice the size of today's average molar are the only remnants of a species we now know lived at the same time and place as modern humans-and interbred with them. They are a part of us we never knew existed. What did these &quot;people&quot; look like? And how do they fit into what we thought we knew about our biological development as a species?

